After years of refusal, Moscow has agreedto discuss the problems of Afghanistan and Kampuchea in itstalks with Peking on normalising relations, ChineseVice-Foreign Minister Qian Qichen said.   He told a news conference: "Recently the Soviet Unionexpressed agreement to discuss this question."    China has long referred to three obstacles to betterrelations -- Soviet troops in Afghanistan, Moscow's support forVietnamese troops in Kampuchea and Soviet troop concentrationsalong the Chinese border. Reuter&#3;